-- Beijing Petroleum Exchange Starts Kerosene, Naphtha, Oil Products Trading
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-08-02T00:47:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-02/beijing-petroleum-exchange-starts-kerosene-naphtha-oil-products-trading.html

          
          
             Beijing Petroleum Exchange began
operations on July 30, and will start spot trading of fuel oil,
kerosene, naphtha, liquefied petroleum gas and lubricants, China
National Petroleum Corp., which has a stake in the exchange,
said in its online newsletter today.  
